<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-03T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="312" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1594.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">Johnson</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-03T19:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 3, 1915—7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your July 6, 11 a.m. Department hopes that President’s special message
                            will have favorable results but in the event of failure nothing should
                            be left undone to prevent the enforcement of the old budget or the
                            enactment of any new budget, carrying appropriations in excess of
                            revenue.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>